  "type": "feat",
  "name": "Improved Treatment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 2nd level, when the medic treats deadly wounds, the creature she treats recovers hit points and ability score damage as if it had rested for a full day and she no longer needs a healer's kit to perform these actions. At 6th level, the medic can treat deadly wounds or provide long term care to a number of creatures equal to her initiation modifier at the same time. In addition, when the medic treats a creature's deadly wounds it recovers hit points as if it had rested for a full day with long term care. At 11th level, when the medic treat deadly wounds, the creature recovers hit point and ability damage as if it had rested for 3 days.</p>",
